#
# This repository is developed with CLI-first defaults to eliminate MCP tool-schema overhead.
# If you are working in an IDE where MCP is required (e.g. JetBrains), prefer MCP tools there.

PREFER lean-ctx CLI commands over MCP tools for token savings (no MCP schema overhead):

| USE (via Shell/Bash) | INSTEAD OF (MCP) | Why |
|---------------------|-------------------|-----|
| `lean-ctx read <path>` | `ctx_read` | No MCP schema overhead, same caching |
| `lean-ctx read <path> -m map` | `ctx_read(mode="map")` | Mode-optimized compressed read |
| `lean-ctx -c "<cmd>"` | `ctx_shell` | Pattern compression (95+ patterns) |
| `lean-ctx grep <pattern> [path]` | `ctx_search` | Compact search results |
| `lean-ctx ls [path]` | `ctx_tree` | Directory maps |

File editing: use native Edit/StrReplace. Write, Delete, Glob → use normally.

<!-- lean-ctx-compression -->
OUTPUT STYLE: dense
- Each statement = one atomic fact line
- Use abbreviations: fn, cfg, impl, deps, req, res, ctx, err, ret
- Diff lines only (+/-/~), never repeat unchanged code
- Symbols: → (causes), + (adds), − (removes), ~ (modifies), ∴ (therefore)
- No narration, no filler, no hedging
- BUDGET: ≤200 tokens per response unless code block required
<!-- /lean-ctx-compression -->
